    public static enum IntPriorityQueue.Mode
extends java.lang.Enum<IntPriorityQueue.Mode>
    Sets the mode used for the priority queue.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      BOUNDED
      Sets the priority queue to use a backing array that indexes into the heap.
      HASH
      Sets the priority queue to use a backing hashtable to map values to their position in the heap.
      STANDARD
      Sets the priority queue to use the standard queue implementation with the standard complexity for the following operations

      O(1) time for IntPriorityQueue.peek()
      O(log n) time for IntPriorityQueue.poll(), AbstractQueue.add(java.lang.Object)
      O(n) time for IntPriorityQueue.remove(java.lang.Object) and IntPriorityQueue.contains(java.lang.Object)
      And calling Iterator.remove() is O(log n), but the iteration is in no particular order

      • HASH

        public static final IntPriorityQueue.Mode HASH
        Sets the priority queue to use a backing hashtable to map values to their position in the heap. This changes the complexity to

        O(1) time for IntPriorityQueue.peek() and IntPriorityQueue.contains(java.lang.Object)
        O(log n) time for IntPriorityQueue.poll(), AbstractQueue.add(java.lang.Object), and IntPriorityQueue.remove(java.lang.Object)
        And calling Iterator.remove() is O(log n), but the iteration is in no particular order

      • BOUNDED

        public static final IntPriorityQueue.Mode BOUNDED
        Sets the priority queue to use a backing array that indexes into the heap. This provides the fastest version if fast IntPriorityQueue.remove(java.lang.Object) and IntPriorityQueue.contains(java.lang.Object) are needed. However, it must create an array as large as the largest int value put into the queue, and negative values will not be accepted. This method is best when the size of the queue is known to be bounded and all values are in the range [0, N].

        O(1) time for IntPriorityQueue.peek() and IntPriorityQueue.contains(java.lang.Object)
        O(log n) time for IntPriorityQueue.poll(), AbstractQueue.add(java.lang.Object), and IntPriorityQueue.remove(java.lang.Object)
        And calling Iterator.remove() is O(log n), but the iteration is in no particular order
